{
  "stem": "719.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That movie theatre still exists, and it has the same name as it used to have then.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], which is something to do with news, with new something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So most of the people knew where I lived, where I grew up, because we had the movie theatre.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And in the very corner, there was a beautiful restaurant, which was very unusual for this town-- modern, very elegant.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And rich people used to-- I used to like to stand outside and watch the rich people, all dressed up with gloves and hats, go into this restaurant.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Because the average people didn't go to restaurants, like in America.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Only the very wealthy ones.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I think that the standard of living was divided into rich and poor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There was very little middle class where I grew up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "That's what I remember, as a child.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And most of the time on the holidays, like Passover, my father would invite some of the children from our floor, from the place where I lived, because I was the only child.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And to him, it was a good deed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It was great to invite if-- a next-door neighbor, or down the hall, somebody had five, six children or more.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he knew how hard food and the cost of living was, so he would ask my mother if it's OK to have somebody to celebrate Passover, or a high holy day, or important holiday with us.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And so that's how I kept a close relationship with one of the boys, which I consider him like my brother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "All the years from my childhood, I felt that he's like my brother.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
